        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 21 at 6:21PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 621 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles northwest of Lubbock International Airport, or 9 miles north of
Lubbock, moving northwest at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lubbock, Abernathy, Wolfforth, Shallowater, Lubbock International
Airport, Texas Tech University, Downtown Lubbock, Lubbock South
Plains Mall, Woodrow, Reese Center, New Deal, and Lubbock Science
Spectrum.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
